## Test Anti-Pattern Audit: `ProductCatalogTests.cs`

### Summary

**10 tests, 10 findings — 7 Critical, 0 High, 3 Medium**

This is a textbook **coverage-touching** test class. Every public method on `ProductCatalog` is called (→ 95% line coverage), but almost nothing is actually verified. These tests will pass even if the production code is completely broken, as long as it doesn't throw.

---

### 🔴 Critical — False Confidence (Fix Immediately)

#### 1. Coverage-touching pattern (systemic)

All 10 tests follow the same formula: call a method, move on. The class walks `ProductCatalog`'s entire API surface in declaration order with no meaningful assertions. This is the root cause of bugs reaching production despite high coverage numbers.

---

#### 2. No assertion — `AddProduct_Works` (line 17)

```csharp
// CURRENT — proves nothing; passes even if Save() silently drops the product
_catalog.AddProduct(product);

// FIX
_catalog.AddProduct(product);
var retrieved = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
Assert.IsNotNull(retrieved);
Assert.AreEqual("Widget", retrieved.Name);
Assert.AreEqual(9.99m, retrieved.Price);
```

#### 3. No assertion — `UpdatePrice_Works` (line 33)

```csharp
// CURRENT — price could stay 9.99 and the test still passes
_catalog.UpdatePrice("SKU-001", 14.99m);

// FIX
_catalog.UpdatePrice("SKU-001", 14.99m);
var updated = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
Assert.AreEqual(14.99m, updated!.Price);
```

#### 4. No assertion — `RemoveProduct_Works` (line 39)

```csharp
// CURRENT — product could still exist after removal
_catalog.RemoveProduct("SKU-001");

// FIX
_catalog.RemoveProduct("SKU-001");
Assert.IsNull(_catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001"));
```

#### 5. No assertion — `GetProductCount_Works` (line 63)

```csharp
// CURRENT — doesn't even capture the return value
var count = _catalog.GetProductCount();

// FIX
_catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
Assert.AreEqual(1, _catalog.GetProductCount());
```

#### 6. No assertion — `ApplyBulkDiscount_Works` (line 69)

```csharp
// CURRENT — a 10% discount could be calculated wrong; test still passes
_catalog.ApplyBulkDiscount(0.10m);

// FIX
_catalog.ApplyBulkDiscount(0.10m);
Assert.AreEqual(8.991m, _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001")!.Price);
Assert.AreEqual(17.991m, _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-002")!.Price);
```

#### 7. No assertion — `ImportFromCsv_Works` (line 85)

